A schema is a named collection of tables. A schema can also contain views, indexes, 
     sequences, data types, operators, and functions.

--- Create schema:
postgres=# create schema dba_schema;
CREATE SCHEMA

-- Create schema with authorize particular user:
postgres=# create schema dba_schema authorization wsc1;
CREATE SCHEMA

-- Drop schema

postgres=# drop schema dba_schema;
DROP SCHEMA

-- List down schemas present

postgres=# \dn+
List of schemas
Name        | Owner.   | Access privileges    | Description
------------+----------+----------------------+------------------------
dba_schema  | wsc1     |                      |
public      | postgres | postgres=UC/postgres+| standard public schema| | =UC/postgres |
wsc         | postgres |                      |
(3 rows)
